  "texts": [
    "It is mainly required in the training phase of motion models and is used for validation purposes during the test phase.",
    "For the present experiments, an angiography scan was used to extract the SI and AP respiratory-induced motion of the target.",
    "The training phase involves acquiring lateral fluoroscopic images of the liver phantom for 30 seconds at 15 frames per second.",
    "The motion of the liver phantom during the training time consisted of 12 seconds of regular breathing, and three 5-second breath-holds at three different phases of the respiratory cycle (target positions).",
    "Simultaneously, the external motion tracked by the EM tracker is measured and used as input for the motion model."
